DM_DAILY.@comment_forecast_24: Install 10 3/4" pack-off and wear bushing. WOC. Run in hole with WL for logging cement. RIH with 8 1/2" BHA and tag TOC.
DM_DAILY.@comment_summary: Ran in hole with 9 5/8" x 10 3/4" casing. Mixed and pumped cement and displaced same. Pressure tested casing. Rigged down casing handling equipment. Washed annulus seal area.

DM_ACTIVITY.@activity_memo: Continued washing annulus seal area with 4000 lpm / 12 bar and 10 rpm.

Installed 10 3/4" pack-off
- Landed of string weight in profile at 39.41 m
- Marked pipe
- TFMC performed quick test to 100 bar to verify seals are holding pressure

Set pack-off with 245 bar using cement pump
- Pressure bled of rapidly 2 times before pressure holding
- String dropped approx 38mm when setting pack-off (expected drop: 46.7mm)
POOH with pack-off running tool.

Ran in hole and installed wear bushing.
- Released from wear bushing with 3 MT

Wait on cement prior to logging
- Meanwhile changed saver sub
- Meanwhile tested pack-off to 20/345 bar for 5/10 min.

Ran in hole with 9 5/8" casing in stands from 1720 to 2366 m
- Hole in good condition.
- Filled every stand
- Running speed 10 m/min
No acitivity in AUX while running casing

Worked casing in hole through tight area from 2366 to 2483 m
- At 2366 m, increase in drag. Set off 20 T in steps, no go. Casing packed off.
- Pulled back with pressure on casing and re-established circulation at 2346 m
- Attempted two times to wash casing in with 400 lpm - nogo.  Casing packed off.
- Attempted to work casing down with increasing set-down weight 25 / 35 ton. 
- Verified free upwards with pressure on casing - observed up to 35 ton OP
- Washed down with 400 lpm from 2340 m to 2378.5 m . Pack off tendencies.
- RIH without pumps from 2378.5 m. Set down max 50 T WOB. Pull up with 20 bar on STP to ensure free upwards and work down with 50 T max WOB.
- Doglegs in area 3.0 - 3.7 deg/30 m.

Ran in hole with 9 5/8" casing in stands from 2483 m to 2955 m
- Hole in good condition
- Filled every stand
- Running speed 10 m/min
- Picked up 9 5/8" single prior to XO

No acitivity in AUX while running casing.
- Prepared stardboard aft bay for upper completion
- Checked 7 remaining stand of 9 5/8" casing prior to running XO stand
Changed handling gear to 10 3/4" and ran in hole with XO stand from 2955 m to 2994 m

Ran in hole with 10 3/4" casing in stands from 2994 m to 3297 m
- Hole in good condition
- Filled every stand
- Running speed 5 m/min
- Changed out PS21 with master bushing on last stand prior to casing hanger
Picked up and made up 10 3/4" casing hanger

Ran in hole on 10 3/4" landing string and landed casing hanger.
- Good indication of landing in WH
- 11 mm drop on WH
- Stick-up: 1.22 m (6 cm high)
Prepare for building 8 1/2" BHA

Circulated to condition mud prior to cementing- Staged up flow in steps of 200 lpm
190lpm - 40bar
390lpm - 47bar
600lpm - 54bar
790lpm - 66bar

Pack-off observed at 790 lpm after 1400 strokes pumped (LCM pill in annulus near Grid fm).  Pressure increased from 66 bar to 75 bar and returns lost. Trapped in 58 bar.

Swap Aux cassette.
Move tong from port to stbd main deck and pick up using jib.
TBT for picking up BHA.

Picked up string 0.5 m and landed off casing hanger in WH, to verify the landing depth. Landed with same stick-up. 
- Stick-up: 1.22 (6 cm high)

Started pumps to determine formation breakdown and stable injection pressure prior to cement job. Pressure broke off at 78 bar and decreased to 48 bar. Continued pre-circulation by increasing flow in 200 lpm steps. No returns to surface.
390 lpm - 77 bar
600 lpm - 51 bar
800 lpm - 51 bar
1000 lpm - 54 bar 
1200 lpm - 53bar
1200 lpm - 53 bar 
1200 lpm - 49 bar
1200 lpm - 45 bar 

Stopped pumps and pulled FC-1 tool out of casing. 25 bar trapped due to check valve in FC-1 tool.
Installed cement head. Established circulation trough cement head with OBM prior to pumping spacer. Verified circulation pressure with 1200 lpm through cement head rig up.

Build 8 ½ BHA
VR plug removed and FMC tested against the RD.
Clear unwanted drilling equipment from Port Aft bay on cantilever.

Pumped 33 m3 of 1.45 sg spacer at 1200 lpm / 35 bar.
- No return observed
- 31 m3 space ahead and 2 m3 spacer left in line.

Mixed and pumped 10.3 m3 of 1.80 sg Expandacem with 800 lpm from cement unit.
- Released bottom plug
- No returns when pumping cement.
- Released top plug
- Displaced cement from cement unit to rigfloor with 400 liters of drill water

Displaced cement with 127.9 m3 of 1.42 sg OBM at 1200 lpm / 20 - 25 bar.
- 2 m3 of spacer behind
- Slight return to trip tank during displacement (1.46 m3/hr gain rate) 
- Bottom plug sheared with 70 bar at 7400 strokes (97.1% efficiency) vs theoretical 7498 strokes (96% efficiency) 
- Observed pressure increase from 30 to 33 bar when cement entered annulus 
- Reduced rate to 500 lpm / 26 bar prior to bumping the top plug
- Top plug landed after 8085 strokes (96.7% efficiency) vs theoretical 8152 strokes (96% efficiency)
- Total volume lost during entire cement job (incl. pre-circulation): 189 m3

Pressure tested casing using mud pumps.
- Pressured up to 46 bar (20 bar above final circulation pressure) and held for 5 min.
- Continued pressuring up to 345 bar and held for 10 min.
- Pumped 2.4 m3 to pressure up from 46 bar to 345 bar and bled back same. 
- Monitored for backflow. Observed backflow decreasing over time.

Rig down after running casing and cementing.
Lift cradles with 5 ½” upper completion to cantilever.
Rigged down cement head

Released casing hanger RT and POOH with landing string
- Released RT with 7 RH turns
- Racked back landing string and laid out casing hanger RT
- Laid out FC-1 tool
Rigged down casing handling equipment

Make up FMC wash tool and run in hole with same
- Tagged with 1 MT 
- Picked up and washed with 4000 lpm / 12 bar and 10 rpm

DM_OPER_EQUIP_FAIL.@failure_description:
Damage  observed on HP riser RX-24 gasket groove (corresponding damage observed on RX-24 gasket removed after D-8 B). 
Installed VR plug before filling riser and proceeding with BOP p-test. 
Offline plan: Damage polished by FMC. Pressure test inner riser drain valve against VR plug. Mobilise PTC VR-tool and remove VR plug. Install out riser drain valve and pressure test.
Repaired damaged rubber pad on chute above longitudinal flowline
Investigated closing signal on Franks BX2 elevator. Adjusted pressure on signal line.
